WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.000
Who is it?

00:03.000 --> 00:05.000
Dad.

00:05.000 --> 00:07.000
Come on in, Dad.

00:07.000 --> 00:11.000
I thought you might be hungry.

00:11.000 --> 00:14.000
I brought you a chicken sandwich, glass of milk.

00:14.000 --> 00:15.000
I am hungry.

00:15.000 --> 00:18.000
Thanks, Dad.

00:18.000 --> 00:22.000
What time is it anyway?

00:22.000 --> 00:25.000
Ten o'clock.

00:25.000 --> 00:27.000
What are you working on?

00:27.000 --> 00:30.000
I am writing a story for the high school paper.

00:30.000 --> 00:32.000
Can't you finish it tomorrow?

00:32.000 --> 00:33.000
No.

00:33.000 --> 00:36.000
I have to turn it in in the morning.

00:36.000 --> 00:38.000
And what's it about?

00:38.000 --> 00:43.000
I am writing an article on the feelings about graduation.

00:43.000 --> 00:46.000
And how do you feel?

00:46.000 --> 00:48.000
Me?

00:48.000 --> 00:50.000
A little scared.

00:50.000 --> 00:53.000
And excited too.

00:53.000 --> 00:55.000
I felt the same way.

00:55.000 --> 00:58.000
Scared parts leaving home and moving to college.

00:58.000 --> 01:00.000
Oh.

01:00.000 --> 01:03.000
Leaving them is part of growing up.

01:03.000 --> 01:06.000
Well, don't work all night.

01:06.000 --> 01:08.000
I don't mind.

01:08.000 --> 01:09.000
I enjoy writing.

01:09.000 --> 01:12.000
Maybe you should think about becoming a writer.

01:12.000 --> 01:14.000
Maybe I should.

01:14.000 --> 01:17.000
You have lots of time to decide.

01:17.000 --> 01:20.000
That's the worst part, making decisions.

01:20.000 --> 01:22.000
You'll be okay.

01:22.000 --> 01:24.000
Good night, son.

01:24.000 --> 01:27.000
Good night, Dad.

01:27.000 --> 01:30.000
Hey, you two, the writers.

01:30.000 --> 01:33.000
I'll be in jail to the conquering heroes.

01:33.000 --> 01:35.000
Hey, you two.

01:35.000 --> 01:38.000
The conquering heroes.

01:38.000 --> 01:39.000
Hey, you two.

01:39.000 --> 01:40.000
The conquering heroes.

01:40.000 --> 01:41.000
Hey, you two.

01:41.000 --> 01:42.000
To the shig.

01:42.000 --> 01:44.000
The champions of the West.

01:44.000 --> 01:46.000
Ha, ha, ha.

01:46.000 --> 01:47.000
Ah, good morning, Robbie.

01:47.000 --> 01:48.000
Good morning, Dad.

01:48.000 --> 01:50.000
How's my grandson?

01:50.000 --> 01:51.000
Fine, grandpa.

01:51.000 --> 01:52.000
Fine.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.000
What's all the cheering about?

01:54.000 --> 01:57.000
Did the University of Michigan win another football game?

01:57.000 --> 01:58.000
Better than that.

01:58.000 --> 02:00.000
Tell me, Philip.

02:00.000 --> 02:04.000
I just spoke with Charlie Raffer, whose Charlie Raffer.

02:04.000 --> 02:07.000
He's the Dean of Admissions for the University of Michigan.

02:07.000 --> 02:10.000
And it turns out, his a classmate of Philip's,

02:10.000 --> 02:12.000
that we were both on the tennis team.

02:12.000 --> 02:14.000
Great.

02:14.000 --> 02:15.000
It is great.

02:15.000 --> 02:18.000
He's going to be in New York tomorrow to interview applicants

02:18.000 --> 02:19.000
for admission.

02:19.000 --> 02:22.000
And he's a great to fit you into his schedule.

02:22.000 --> 02:25.000
But I may not want to go to Michigan.

02:25.000 --> 02:28.000
It's one of the best schools in the country, Robbie.

02:28.000 --> 02:29.000
I studied medicine there.

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
Your grandfather went to the engineering school there.

02:32.000 --> 02:33.000
I know that.

02:33.000 --> 02:37.000
But you said you wanted to be a doctor like your father?

02:37.000 --> 02:38.000
Not exactly.

02:38.000 --> 02:42.000
You couldn't pick a finer medical school than Michigan.

02:42.000 --> 02:43.000
Yes, I know that.

02:43.000 --> 02:46.000
Let's meet with Charlie at the University Club.

02:46.000 --> 02:48.000
10 o'clock tomorrow morning.

02:48.000 --> 02:51.000
It doesn't mean you're going to Michigan.

02:51.000 --> 02:53.000
It doesn't mean you have to be a doctor.

02:53.000 --> 02:57.000
But the interviewer would be good experience for you.

02:57.000 --> 02:59.000
In that case, it's OK.

02:59.000 --> 03:05.000
Dad, growing up means making my own decisions, doesn't it?

03:05.000 --> 03:08.000
You're right, Robbie.

03:08.000 --> 03:14.000
But like your grandpa suggested, have the interview.

03:14.000 --> 03:17.000
And then make your own decision.

03:17.000 --> 03:19.000
That sounds fine.

03:19.000 --> 03:21.000
Look, I know it's sudden, Robbie.

03:21.000 --> 03:23.000
But this is an important opportunity.

03:23.000 --> 03:26.000
We'll head down there first thing tomorrow morning.

03:26.000 --> 03:27.000
OK.

03:27.000 --> 03:28.000
Sure, Dad.

03:28.000 --> 03:32.000
I want you to know something, son.

03:32.000 --> 03:38.000
I'm very proud of you.

03:38.000 --> 03:40.000
Thanks, Dad.

03:40.000 --> 03:45.000
Well, I've got an appointment at the hospital.

03:45.000 --> 03:47.000
I'll see you all at dinner time.

03:47.000 --> 03:50.000
Bye, Dad.

03:50.000 --> 03:55.000
Is there something still wrong, Robbie?

03:55.000 --> 03:58.000
I'll be OK.

03:58.000 --> 04:06.000
Going away to college for the first time always makes one a little nervous.

04:06.000 --> 04:07.000
I guess so.

04:07.000 --> 04:09.000
I'll be OK.

04:09.000 --> 04:11.000
It's just need time to think.

